{% extends "_base.j2" %}

{% block physics_section %}
PHYSICS
The ball moves with integer velocity (vx, vy). Starting speed is |vx|=1.
Every 6 paddle hits, |vx| increases by 1 (max 2). The ball bounces off the
top and bottom walls (vy flips). On paddle hit, vx flips and vy is set based
on where the ball hits the paddle (-1 for top, 0 for center, +1 for bottom).

The HUD shows the ball's exact position and velocity each turn. Use this to
predict where the ball will arrive and position your paddle accordingly.

SERVE
Press FIRE (or UP_FIRE/DOWN_FIRE) to serve. Until you serve, the ball stays
at center and your paddle can still move with UP/DOWN.

OPPONENT
The AI opponent tracks the ball 70% of the time and stays still 30%.
{% endblock %}
